name: r-golem
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-golem
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/golem_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/golem/golem_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9ea921ca108d7ac9a2b21cec29e6ec6e176a7fda49654d0a0fcd7a7d68f3fc2c

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-attempt
    - r-cli
    - r-config
    - r-crayon
    - r-desc
    - r-dockerfiler
    - r-fs
    - r-here
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-pkgload
    - r-remotes
    - r-rlang
    - r-roxygen2
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-shiny
    - r-testthat
    - r-usethis
    - r-yaml
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-attempt
    - r-cli
    - r-config
    - r-crayon
    - r-desc
    - r-dockerfiler
    - r-fs
    - r-here
    - r-htmltools
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-pkgload
    - r-remotes
    - r-rlang
    - r-roxygen2
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-shiny
    - r-testthat
    - r-usethis
    - r-yaml

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('golem')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('golem')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ThinkR-open/golem
  license: MIT
  summary: An opinionated framework for building a production-ready 'Shiny' application. This package contains a series of tools for building a robust 'Shiny' application from start to finish.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
